<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note17" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Eumenes*.html#ref17
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">17</A>
Antipater, Craterus and Ptolemy had declared war against Perdiccas. The destruction of Perdiccas' ally, Eumenes, was a side issue. Perdiccas, taking with him Arrhidaeus and Roxana and her infant son, had already invaded


<A ID="p95x"></A>Egypt in an attempt to destroy Ptolemy. Antipater was hastening to the aid of Ptolemy.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note18" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Eumenes*.html#ref18
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
